1
00:00:36,403 --> 00:00:39,304
ADULT ANTONIO: Why is
there evil in the world?

2
00:00:39,372 --> 00:00:41,806
Let me start
from the beginning,

3
00:00:42,575 --> 00:00:46,909
when I was innocent of the
ways of God, and men.

4
00:00:48,248 --> 00:00:50,648
It was the summer
when I was seven.

5
00:00:51,818 --> 00:00:54,013
The summer Ultima came to us.

6
00:01:06,566 --> 00:01:10,468
Papa! Mama! Mama!

7
00:01:11,304 --> 00:01:12,999
Mama, they're coming!

8
00:01:14,541 --> 00:01:17,806
Deborah! Theresa!
They're here.

9
00:01:20,146 --> 00:01:22,080
Is Ultima really a witch?

10
00:01:22,148 --> 00:01:24,514
No. And you will call
her La Grande.

11
00:01:25,752 --> 00:01:27,845
I'm afraid.
Mind your manners!

12
00:01:27,921 --> 00:01:30,389
We are honored that she
comes to live with us.

13
00:01:33,593 --> 00:01:35,185
(BRAKES SQUEAL)

14
00:01:37,797 --> 00:01:39,059
(CAR DOOR SHUTS)

15
00:01:41,434 --> 00:01:43,425
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

16
00:01:43,670 --> 00:01:48,630
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

17
00:01:48,942 --> 00:01:50,705
(BOTH CHUCKLE) Come, come.

18
00:01:52,612 --> 00:01:53,874
(GREETING IN SPANISH)

19
00:01:58,485 --> 00:01:59,816
(GREETING IN SPANISH)

20
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:03,248
What beautiful daughters
you have raised. (LAUGHS)

21
00:02:03,990 --> 00:02:05,048
Toño.

22
00:02:12,665 --> 00:02:13,927
Antonio.

23
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:26,039
Antonio?

24
00:02:28,848 --> 00:02:31,009
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

25
00:02:31,217 --> 00:02:33,617
Antonio, Grande.
ULTIMA: Let it be.

26
00:02:35,588 --> 00:02:39,115
This was the last child
I pulled from your womb.

27
00:02:40,059 --> 00:02:42,653
I knew there would be
something between us.

28
00:02:44,931 --> 00:02:48,492
I've come to spend the last
days of my life here, Antonio.

29
00:02:51,271 --> 00:02:53,262
You will never die.
I'll take care of you.

30
00:02:53,573 --> 00:02:55,837
(CHUCKLING)
(GABRIEL SPEAKING SPANISH)

31
00:02:56,876 --> 00:02:58,605
(CONTINUES IN SPANISH)

32
00:02:59,312 --> 00:03:02,213
It's too hot to be standing out
here and chatting all day.

33
00:03:11,524 --> 00:03:13,014
THERESA: She's a bruja!

34
00:03:13,126 --> 00:03:15,651
They sometimes
become owls at night.

35
00:03:16,129 --> 00:03:20,156
DEBORAH: Mama says she's not a witch.
She's a curandera.

36
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:22,658
She won't hurt you.

37
00:03:22,735 --> 00:03:25,363
THERESA: Why does
she have to live with us?

38
00:03:25,438 --> 00:03:28,737
DEBORAH: Mama says she has no family.
Now, go to sleep.

39
00:03:28,808 --> 00:03:30,400
(OWL HOOTING)

40
00:04:00,907 --> 00:04:03,171
(OWL HOOTING)

41
00:04:04,911 --> 00:04:06,503
(BANGING ON DOOR)

42
00:04:08,548 --> 00:04:09,572
MAN: Marez!

43
00:04:10,416 --> 00:04:12,316
(BANGING CONTINUES)
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

44
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:19,021
Mi hermano! He killed my brother!
(ENQUIRING IN SPANISH)

45
00:04:19,759 --> 00:04:21,556
Lupito! Lupito shot him!

46
00:04:21,861 --> 00:04:25,456
Lupito? No, no.
No, I don't believe it!

47
00:04:25,531 --> 00:04:26,691
Go get your rifle.

48
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:28,757
The other ones
are at the bridge.

49
00:04:28,835 --> 00:04:30,427
The bridge?
He took to the river.

50
00:04:30,570 --> 00:04:31,867
(WHISPERS) Qué pasó, Antonio?

51
00:04:31,971 --> 00:04:33,097
(SHUSHING)

52
00:04:33,473 --> 00:04:36,965
My brother was just at that
bus depot having coffee,

53
00:04:37,043 --> 00:04:40,012
when that guy went up to where he was
and shot him in the back of the head.

54
00:04:40,179 --> 00:04:42,044
Oh, Dios, be careful, Gabriel.

55
00:04:42,448 --> 00:04:43,608
(GABRIEL AGREEING IN SPANISH)

56
00:04:43,916 --> 00:04:45,281
I'm sorry.

57
00:04:46,419 --> 00:04:48,683
Maria, lock the door.

58
00:04:48,755 --> 00:04:50,689
Ese Lupito,
the war's made him crazy.

59
00:04:51,324 --> 00:04:53,053
(LOCKING DOOR)

60
00:04:55,261 --> 00:04:56,888
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

61
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:03,091
Antonio, what are you doing?

62
00:05:04,570 --> 00:05:05,832
I'm gonna tell.

63
00:05:06,039 --> 00:05:08,371
(MARIA PRAYING)

64
00:05:30,630 --> 00:05:31,961
(OWL HOOTING)

65
00:05:39,105 --> 00:05:41,198
(MEN TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

66
00:05:44,610 --> 00:05:47,545
Could be on the other side.
Hey. Yeah.

67
00:05:52,452 --> 00:05:54,420
MAN 1: What about
the tall brush over there?

68
00:05:54,487 --> 00:05:56,717
MAN 2: You gonna make
up the clearance?

69
00:05:59,826 --> 00:06:00,952
(TWIGS SNAPPING)

70
00:06:04,764 --> 00:06:06,823
Ssh! Did you hear that?

71
00:06:14,707 --> 00:06:16,265
He's there!
There! There!

72
00:06:16,342 --> 00:06:19,505
Run! Japanese soldiers!
Japanese soldiers!

73
00:06:33,726 --> 00:06:35,387
NARCISO: Put
those rifles away!

74
00:06:35,461 --> 00:06:36,792
No! He's down there!

75
00:06:36,863 --> 00:06:38,922
He's an animal.
He's gotta be shot!

76
00:06:38,998 --> 00:06:40,727
No! We need
to talk to him!

77
00:06:40,967 --> 00:06:44,425
Marez is right.
Marez is right!

78
00:06:44,604 --> 00:06:47,402
Por Dios, hombres!
Let us act like men!

79
00:06:47,473 --> 00:06:49,441
That's Lupito out there!

80
00:06:49,776 --> 00:06:51,175
You all know Lupito.

81
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:53,337
You know the war made him sick!

82
00:06:53,413 --> 00:06:55,404
Go back to your drinking,
Narciso.

83
00:06:55,481 --> 00:06:56,641
Leave this job to men.

84
00:06:57,350 --> 00:07:00,217
That animal crawled behind my
brother, and took his life.

85
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:02,613
He's gotta be destroyed!
Wait!

86
00:07:02,955 --> 00:07:04,081
(GRUNTING)

87
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:06,251
I will talk to him!

88
00:07:07,627 --> 00:07:10,994
Lupito!
It's me, Narciso!

89
00:07:11,964 --> 00:07:13,864
Listen, my friend.

90
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:17,261
A very bad business
has happened tonight.

91
00:07:18,204 --> 00:07:21,435
Let me come down
and talk to you.

92
00:07:22,475 --> 00:07:24,067
Let me help you.

93
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:27,470
Remember before
you went to the war.

94
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:32,749
When you first came into the
Eight Ball to gamble a little?

95
00:07:33,319 --> 00:07:34,877
Remember how I taught you

96
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:37,650
how Juan Botas marked the aces

97
00:07:37,723 --> 00:07:41,887
with a little tobacco juice,
and how you beat him?

98
00:07:42,962 --> 00:07:45,931
Those were good times, Lupito!

99
00:07:46,966 --> 00:07:49,457
Those were good times!

100
00:08:00,513 --> 00:08:01,980
(SCREAMING)

101
00:08:02,648 --> 00:08:03,774
That's your answer!

102
00:08:06,519 --> 00:08:07,918
(WHIMPERING)

103
00:08:33,546 --> 00:08:34,843
(GUNS COCKING)

104
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:58,860
(GASPING)

105
00:09:01,607 --> 00:09:03,074
Bless me.

106
00:09:21,394 --> 00:09:23,385
(MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

107
00:09:28,768 --> 00:09:31,100
I'm heartily sorry
for having offended Thee,

108
00:09:31,170 --> 00:09:34,606
and I detest all my sins because
of Thy just punishments.

109
00:09:34,674 --> 00:09:37,700
Oh, my God, I'm heartily sorry
for having offended Thee.

110
00:09:37,877 --> 00:09:39,606
(OWL HOOTING)

111
00:10:04,170 --> 00:10:05,296
You knew.

112
00:10:07,907 --> 00:10:09,204
Yes.

113
00:10:13,646 --> 00:10:16,672
They killed Lupito.
Will he go to Hell?

114
00:10:16,983 --> 00:10:18,678
That's not for us to say.

115
00:10:33,699 --> 00:10:35,724
And the men on the bridge?

116
00:10:36,969 --> 00:10:38,129
Papa?

117
00:10:38,337 --> 00:10:40,328
Men will do as they must.

118
00:11:08,367 --> 00:11:10,301
MARIA: Gabriel, get up!

119
00:11:46,872 --> 00:11:48,464
(SPANISH SONG PLAYING)

120
00:11:54,513 --> 00:11:56,037
Go, go. We go.

121
00:11:58,684 --> 00:12:00,481
(WOMAN SPEAKING SPANISH)

122
00:12:19,905 --> 00:12:21,065
(BOY SPEAKING SPANISH)

123
00:12:24,744 --> 00:12:26,336
(GREETING IN SPANISH)

124
00:12:32,051 --> 00:12:33,575
La bruja.

125
00:12:33,652 --> 00:12:35,210
(CONTINUES IN SPANISH)

126
00:12:36,522 --> 00:12:38,990
Hey. Hombre!

127
00:12:39,458 --> 00:12:41,050
(APOLOGIZING IN SPANISH)

128
00:12:44,096 --> 00:12:45,256
I don't believe you.

129
00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:47,357
(BOYS EXCLAIMING)

130
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:48,559
(CUSSING IN SPANISH)

131
00:12:50,035 --> 00:12:51,525
Hey, there's that kid again.

132
00:12:53,939 --> 00:12:56,169
Hey, kid, come here.

133
00:12:59,779 --> 00:13:02,407
What, you scared or something?
Come on!

134
00:13:10,990 --> 00:13:12,184
(GRUNTING)

135
00:13:12,258 --> 00:13:14,089
Darn, did you see that?

136
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:16,060
BOY: Whoa!
The kid threw me!

137
00:13:18,531 --> 00:13:20,089
They call me Horse.
Shake hands.

138
00:13:21,467 --> 00:13:22,900
No, thanks.
Smart kid.

139
00:13:23,068 --> 00:13:24,296
Shut up!

140
00:13:24,436 --> 00:13:27,303
Listen, kid, don't think you
could do it again, understand?

141
00:13:27,373 --> 00:13:28,863
(GIRL SPEAKING SPANISH)

142
00:13:28,974 --> 00:13:30,635
Mass is starting!

143
00:13:44,857 --> 00:13:47,382
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

144
00:13:48,093 --> 00:13:51,221
We are very
lucky today. Mira.

145
00:13:53,399 --> 00:13:55,060
Gordolobo.

146
00:13:55,134 --> 00:13:59,127
Good for throat and lung,
fever, infections.

147
00:13:59,471 --> 00:14:01,302
No, no, no!
Speak to it.

148
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:04,871
It is alive, like all things,

149
00:14:04,944 --> 00:14:09,847
like the trees,
the rocks, the river...

150
00:14:10,249 --> 00:14:14,777
You must speak to it before you
take it from its home. Mira.

151
00:14:16,222 --> 00:14:19,953
To all you who dwell
here by the river.

152
00:14:20,926 --> 00:14:23,121
You that dwell here
by the river.

153
00:14:23,596 --> 00:14:26,326
ULTIMA: We lift you
to make good medicine.

154
00:14:26,832 --> 00:14:29,266
ANTONIO: We lift you
to make good medicine.

155
00:14:30,436 --> 00:14:33,269
ADULT ANTONIO: There is a
beauty in the time of day,

156
00:14:33,339 --> 00:14:35,466
and the time of night,

157
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:39,174
and there is peace in the
river and in the hills.

158
00:14:39,979 --> 00:14:43,881
Ultima taught me to listen to the
mystery of the living earth,

159
00:14:43,949 --> 00:14:48,079
and to feel complete in the
fulfillment of its time.

160
00:14:48,153 --> 00:14:49,745
(CHUCKLING)

161
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:02,265
What's that?

162
00:15:03,869 --> 00:15:05,837
It's the spirit of the river.

163
00:15:07,339 --> 00:15:08,772
Can it speak?

164
00:15:08,841 --> 00:15:11,139
Yes, listen.

165
00:15:18,984 --> 00:15:20,451
What's it saying?

166
00:15:21,854 --> 00:15:25,415
(CHUCKLING) Ay, my child,
you want to know so much.

167
00:15:55,654 --> 00:15:57,121
Toño.

168
00:15:57,189 --> 00:15:59,282
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

169
00:16:00,225 --> 00:16:01,749
(GRUNTING)

170
00:16:07,166 --> 00:16:08,326
Pedro!

171
00:16:09,234 --> 00:16:10,997
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

172
00:16:12,604 --> 00:16:15,232
And La Grande, you know,
has come to live with us.

173
00:16:15,741 --> 00:16:17,140
(PEDRO GREETING IN SPANISH)

174
00:16:18,711 --> 00:16:20,178
Papa sends
his blessings to you.

175
00:16:20,446 --> 00:16:22,107
(THANKS IN SPANISH)

176
00:16:22,414 --> 00:16:24,541
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

177
00:16:31,924 --> 00:16:33,414
How is Papa?

178
00:16:33,492 --> 00:16:35,892
He's well.
He sends his love.

179
00:16:36,061 --> 00:16:37,619
And our brothers?

180
00:16:39,198 --> 00:16:43,828
Um, Lucas, he's...
He's very bad.

181
00:16:45,604 --> 00:16:48,232
Even the great doctor
in Santa Fe cannot help him.

182
00:16:49,742 --> 00:16:52,267
A few of our cows
wandered away, so...

183
00:16:53,112 --> 00:16:54,832
So Lucas crossed the river
to look for them.

184
00:16:58,384 --> 00:17:01,842
(SIGHS) He walked toward
a grove of cottonwood trees.

185
00:17:02,421 --> 00:17:03,615
An evil place.

186
00:17:05,024 --> 00:17:06,585
He'd been warned before
not to go there,

187
00:17:06,658 --> 00:17:09,126
but, Lucas, he...
He doesn't listen.

188
00:17:10,195 --> 00:17:11,890
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

189
00:17:14,633 --> 00:17:17,193
He came up on the three daughters
of Tenorio Trementina.

190
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:23,267
(CHANTING IN SPANISH)

191
00:17:28,247 --> 00:17:31,148
He saw them pour the blood of a
beheaded rooster into a pot.

192
00:17:32,584 --> 00:17:36,213
(CHANTING IN SPANISH)

193
00:17:37,489 --> 00:17:39,457
(SIGHS) Within the week
he got sick.

194
00:17:40,426 --> 00:17:44,658
And now so many weeks later,
he lies in bed wasting away.

195
00:17:44,763 --> 00:17:46,094
(MARIA GASPS)

196
00:17:46,165 --> 00:17:47,223
He's dying.

197
00:17:48,967 --> 00:17:50,525
MARIA: Did you go
to the priest?

198
00:17:51,537 --> 00:17:53,297
PEDRO: The priest came
and blessed the house.

199
00:17:53,305 --> 00:17:54,772
You know, the priest
in El Puerto, he...

200
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:57,001
He washes his hands
of the whole matter.

201
00:17:57,076 --> 00:17:58,338
(SNIFFLING)

202
00:17:59,344 --> 00:18:00,743
Ay, Pedro Luna,

203
00:18:01,046 --> 00:18:05,574
you're like an old lady who sits and
talks, and wastes valuable time!

204
00:18:05,684 --> 00:18:06,912
You will go?

205
00:18:10,989 --> 00:18:13,480
Yes, I will go.

206
00:18:14,326 --> 00:18:19,263
But you must understand, that when
one tampers with the fate of a man,

207
00:18:20,332 --> 00:18:24,701
a chain of events is set in
motion that no one can control.

208
00:18:26,538 --> 00:18:29,006
Can you accept
that responsibility?

209
00:18:32,411 --> 00:18:36,313
Sí. On behalf of my brothers.
Good.

210
00:18:36,682 --> 00:18:38,809
Antonio will have
to go with me.

211
00:18:38,884 --> 00:18:41,318
What? What for? Why?

212
00:18:41,420 --> 00:18:43,888
ULTIMA: It must be so, if you
want your brother cured.

213
00:18:45,924 --> 00:18:48,324
It will be good for
Antonio to see his uncle.

214
00:18:48,427 --> 00:18:50,395
He's not going to visit.

215
00:18:50,462 --> 00:18:51,793
Antonio?

216
00:18:52,731 --> 00:18:54,892
Antonio, you wanna
help your uncle?

217
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:56,093
(AGREES IN SPANISH)

218
00:18:56,702 --> 00:19:00,069
And if someone says that
you walk with a curandera,

219
00:19:00,139 --> 00:19:01,834
will you be ashamed?

220
00:19:01,940 --> 00:19:03,601
No, Ultima.
I will be proud.

221
00:19:04,476 --> 00:19:06,205
Good! Let's go.

222
00:19:06,578 --> 00:19:08,808
We waste precious time.

223
00:19:27,332 --> 00:19:29,357
ULTIMA: It's a good sign.

224
00:19:30,135 --> 00:19:33,036
They call this valley
El Puerto de la Luna.

225
00:19:33,605 --> 00:19:35,573
Because it is the door
through which the moon

226
00:19:35,641 --> 00:19:39,077
passes on its journey
from the east to the west.

227
00:20:02,434 --> 00:20:04,026
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

228
00:20:08,473 --> 00:20:09,667
Hola, Grandpa.

229
00:20:09,741 --> 00:20:11,333
(GREETING IN SPANISH)

230
00:20:12,878 --> 00:20:18,214
Médica, my son is dying.

231
00:20:19,851 --> 00:20:22,285
Abuelo, I have the cure
for your son.

232
00:20:22,387 --> 00:20:23,684
Like old times.

233
00:20:24,489 --> 00:20:27,458
I will pay you in silver
if you save my son's life.

234
00:20:27,526 --> 00:20:29,721
$40 to cheat la muerte.

235
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:38,496
It's been many years since a
curandera has come to cure.

236
00:20:39,705 --> 00:20:42,674
There are women who are already
mourning your son's death.

237
00:20:43,442 --> 00:20:44,568
Ah, neighbors.

238
00:20:45,677 --> 00:20:47,110
Get rid of them.

239
00:20:47,212 --> 00:20:49,442
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

240
00:20:54,953 --> 00:20:58,753
Is Tenorio in his dog hole
that he calls a saloon?

241
00:20:59,024 --> 00:21:00,116
Wait!

242
00:21:00,192 --> 00:21:02,490
I'll have Pedro and Juan
go with you.

243
00:21:02,561 --> 00:21:05,223
I don't need them
to deal with Tenorio.

244
00:21:05,964 --> 00:21:07,329
My grandson!

245
00:21:07,899 --> 00:21:11,630
Antonio goes with me.
Venga, mijo.

246
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:33,155
Are you afraid, Antonio?

247
00:21:35,027 --> 00:21:36,494
No.

248
00:21:37,929 --> 00:21:39,556
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

249
00:21:48,407 --> 00:21:49,999
TENORIO: Show me
what you have.

250
00:21:50,075 --> 00:21:51,474
(MAN SPEAKING SPANISH)

251
00:21:52,544 --> 00:21:54,409
Tenorio Trementina!

252
00:21:58,884 --> 00:22:01,352
Are you afraid
to face an old woman?

253
00:22:05,190 --> 00:22:06,657
What do you want, bruja?

254
00:22:06,725 --> 00:22:08,022
(LAUGHS)

255
00:22:08,093 --> 00:22:09,526
Ay, Tenorio.

256
00:22:09,594 --> 00:22:11,926
You're as ugly
as the devil will allow.

257
00:22:12,030 --> 00:22:14,396
(ALL LAUGHING)

258
00:22:14,533 --> 00:22:16,296
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

259
00:22:16,368 --> 00:22:18,029
I am a curandera.

260
00:22:18,637 --> 00:22:21,333
It's your daughters
who are witches.

261
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:24,702
(SCOFFS) You lie, vieja!

262
00:22:25,043 --> 00:22:28,035
Tenorio, I know
about the curse.

263
00:22:28,613 --> 00:22:31,275
And I know when
and where it was laid.

264
00:22:31,850 --> 00:22:35,115
And you're a fool if you
don't tell them to lift it.

265
00:22:35,854 --> 00:22:40,848
Bruja! You shame my daughters and
my good name in front of these men.

266
00:22:42,527 --> 00:22:44,358
I will see you dead.

267
00:22:45,130 --> 00:22:47,257
Don't threaten me, Tenorio.

268
00:22:47,999 --> 00:22:50,365
You well know the power
of my medicine.

269
00:22:50,502 --> 00:22:51,935
(GREETING IN SPANISH)

270
00:22:54,439 --> 00:22:56,498
I tried to reason with you.

271
00:22:56,942 --> 00:22:59,274
Do not harm
my daughters, bruja!

272
00:23:00,412 --> 00:23:03,108
ULTIMA: They chose
to tamper with fate.

273
00:23:03,281 --> 00:23:05,340
Pity the consequences.

274
00:23:15,293 --> 00:23:16,658
(WIND HOWLING)

275
00:23:22,901 --> 00:23:24,163
I grew worried.

276
00:23:24,770 --> 00:23:26,294
La curandera!

277
00:23:27,739 --> 00:23:29,104
ULTIMA:
Is everything ready?

278
00:23:29,174 --> 00:23:30,454
(GRANDFATHER AGREEING
IN SPANISH)

279
00:23:36,148 --> 00:23:38,673
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

280
00:23:44,790 --> 00:23:46,052
(WISHING LUCK IN SPANISH)

281
00:23:50,362 --> 00:23:51,693
(DOOR OPENS)

282
00:23:52,697 --> 00:23:53,755
Lucas.

283
00:23:56,535 --> 00:23:59,003
He has been like that
for the last two weeks.

284
00:23:59,237 --> 00:24:00,670
Beyond hope.

285
00:24:00,739 --> 00:24:02,673
ULTIMA: Life is never
beyond hope.

286
00:24:03,942 --> 00:24:05,910
Go. Go now.

287
00:24:07,846 --> 00:24:10,110
Antonio, make the fire.

288
00:24:12,584 --> 00:24:17,112
It'll be difficult.
They made him wait too long.

289
00:24:18,123 --> 00:24:19,750
Why did they wait?

290
00:24:20,926 --> 00:24:24,054
The priest would not allow your
grandfather to send for me.

291
00:24:24,796 --> 00:24:26,263
He's afraid of Tenorio.

292
00:24:27,799 --> 00:24:29,699
Drink, Lucas.
(GROANING)

293
00:24:30,869 --> 00:24:34,999
Drink. Un poquito.
Un poquito, Lucas.

294
00:24:35,073 --> 00:24:37,633
(CONTINUES GROANING)
Drink. Lucas.

295
00:24:37,709 --> 00:24:40,109
Lucas, drink this.
Un poquito.

296
00:24:41,112 --> 00:24:44,343
I believe they had his fresh
cut hair to work with.

297
00:24:46,318 --> 00:24:50,652
The curse is very strong,
and his strength is gone.

298
00:24:51,523 --> 00:24:52,990
Will he die?

299
00:24:53,458 --> 00:24:55,585
ULTIMA:
They stole his soul.

300
00:24:56,795 --> 00:24:57,955
We must get it back.

301
00:24:58,029 --> 00:25:01,863
At the cantina, you weren't
afraid of Tenorio.

302
00:25:01,933 --> 00:25:03,594
No, mijito.

303
00:25:03,869 --> 00:25:06,303
Good is always
stronger than evil.

304
00:25:06,938 --> 00:25:09,133
Always remember that, Antonio.

305
00:25:09,574 --> 00:25:11,201
The smallest bit of good

306
00:25:11,276 --> 00:25:14,677
can stand against all the
powers of evil in the world.

307
00:25:14,813 --> 00:25:16,474
(DISTANT HOWLING)

308
00:25:24,990 --> 00:25:28,585
(LAUGHS) Oh, those,
Trementina girls

309
00:25:28,660 --> 00:25:31,493
will be all cut and
bruised in the morning.

310
00:25:38,603 --> 00:25:40,036
(WIND BLOWING)

311
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:44,101
(GROANING)

312
00:25:46,811 --> 00:25:48,506
(GRUNTING)

313
00:25:53,752 --> 00:25:56,414
(GROANING)

314
00:26:12,804 --> 00:26:15,034
Ultima. Ultima.

315
00:26:20,612 --> 00:26:23,877
Ultima. Ultima.

316
00:26:30,322 --> 00:26:32,153
(OWL HOOTING)

317
00:26:33,825 --> 00:26:35,190
(OWL SCREECHES)
(GASPS)

318
00:26:42,834 --> 00:26:44,267
(DOOR OPENS)

319
00:26:46,137 --> 00:26:47,798
There is no fever.

320
00:26:48,673 --> 00:26:51,506
The blood of the Lunas
is strong in you.

321
00:26:52,577 --> 00:26:54,943
We have beaten
the death spirit.

322
00:26:55,013 --> 00:26:59,609
Now, all that remains is for
him to vomit the curse.

323
00:27:05,557 --> 00:27:06,922
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

324
00:27:09,694 --> 00:27:11,389
You have done evil.

325
00:27:13,298 --> 00:27:17,359
But good is stronger than evil,

326
00:27:18,169 --> 00:27:20,262
and the evil you did

327
00:27:22,440 --> 00:27:25,409
will fly in your faces.

328
00:27:26,011 --> 00:27:27,774
(SHIVERING)

329
00:27:30,515 --> 00:27:32,005
(MOANING)

330
00:27:41,259 --> 00:27:42,453
(GROANING)

331
00:27:56,007 --> 00:28:00,410
Lucas. Lucas.
Drink this.

332
00:28:01,546 --> 00:28:04,014
There we go, just a
little, just a little.

333
00:28:04,082 --> 00:28:05,276
(LUCAS GROANS)

334
00:28:06,151 --> 00:28:08,278
(YELLING)
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

335
00:28:08,353 --> 00:28:10,548
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

336
00:28:14,025 --> 00:28:15,822
(SCREAMING)

337
00:28:15,994 --> 00:28:18,895
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

338
00:28:21,800 --> 00:28:22,926
(GROANING)

339
00:28:23,334 --> 00:28:26,326
Let it out. Let it out.
Let it out! Let it out!

340
00:28:27,972 --> 00:28:29,200
Ah.

341
00:28:33,144 --> 00:28:34,543
(SOBBING)

342
00:28:45,290 --> 00:28:48,782
We will burn this by the tree
where the witches dance.

343
00:29:04,075 --> 00:29:06,270
Your son lives, old man.

344
00:29:22,360 --> 00:29:23,759
Papa.

345
00:29:26,231 --> 00:29:27,630
Lucas!

346
00:29:31,035 --> 00:29:32,468
(THANKING GOD IN SPANISH)

347
00:29:32,837 --> 00:29:35,169
Do not tire him
too much at first.

348
00:29:35,874 --> 00:29:39,207
(THANKING IN SPANISH)

349
00:29:40,278 --> 00:29:44,772
Médica, I can never repay you
for saving my son's life.

350
00:29:45,450 --> 00:29:48,681
Perhaps someday
the men of El Puerto

351
00:29:50,321 --> 00:29:52,016
will save my life.

352
00:29:54,192 --> 00:29:56,888
Antonio, vámonos.

353
00:30:17,448 --> 00:30:18,472
(THANKING IN SPANISH)

354
00:30:18,750 --> 00:30:20,308
We must burn this.

355
00:30:33,064 --> 00:30:36,124
ADULT ANTONIO: The doctors and
their medicines had failed.

356
00:30:36,701 --> 00:30:38,760
The priests had failed.

357
00:30:39,204 --> 00:30:42,298
ULTIMA: Take us to the river where
Lucas saw the witches dance.

358
00:30:42,373 --> 00:30:43,635
(AGREEING SPANISH)

359
00:30:44,676 --> 00:30:48,305
ADULT ANTONIO: Was Ultima's
magic stronger than the saints?

360
00:30:48,479 --> 00:30:50,538
And the Holy Mother Church?

361
00:30:50,949 --> 00:30:53,110
It was Mauricio's oldest boy.

362
00:30:53,451 --> 00:30:55,749
He was crushed
beneath a tractor.

363
00:30:55,820 --> 00:30:56,912
That's right.

364
00:30:57,021 --> 00:30:58,682
He... He worked the potato
fields in Colorado.

365
00:30:58,756 --> 00:31:02,783
VAQUERO: Now, his other boy,
he runs whiskey in Texas.

366
00:31:02,861 --> 00:31:05,989
You know, to the cotton
fields in the dry counties.

367
00:31:06,164 --> 00:31:08,189
Mauricio? Does he
run whiskey too?

368
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:11,194
Mauricio? He just runs
from his wife.

369
00:31:11,269 --> 00:31:13,328
(ALL LAUGHING)

370
00:31:13,538 --> 00:31:16,268
ADULT ANTONIO: When my father's
friends, the vaqueros came to town,

371
00:31:17,008 --> 00:31:19,476
they always found
their way to our table.

372
00:31:19,711 --> 00:31:22,908
I liked to watch my father
reminisce about the old times,

373
00:31:22,981 --> 00:31:25,313
because for a while
he was happy.

374
00:31:26,251 --> 00:31:28,913
Other times he'd curse the war
that had taken my brothers

375
00:31:29,020 --> 00:31:30,954
so far away from home,

376
00:31:31,022 --> 00:31:33,991
and from his dream of moving
us all to California.

377
00:31:34,292 --> 00:31:35,486
When do you plan to go?

378
00:31:35,860 --> 00:31:38,385
When my boys come back
from the war.

379
00:31:39,597 --> 00:31:40,791
Then we'll all go together.

380
00:31:41,599 --> 00:31:43,599
You know, there's... There's
lots of work out there,

381
00:31:43,635 --> 00:31:45,227
and now with the war and all.

382
00:31:45,503 --> 00:31:47,368
As I said, there's work
in Texas too!

383
00:31:47,605 --> 00:31:48,799
(ALL LAUGHING)

384
00:31:48,873 --> 00:31:50,738
(TOASTING IN SPANISH)

385
00:31:51,542 --> 00:31:52,975
GABRIEL: Oh!

386
00:32:01,085 --> 00:32:02,950
MARIA:
My man of learning.

387
00:32:03,087 --> 00:32:04,418
The last one to leave me.

388
00:32:04,555 --> 00:32:06,489
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

389
00:32:06,557 --> 00:32:09,788
♪ Tony's going to school! ♪
Theresa, stop!

390
00:32:10,695 --> 00:32:12,390
He should be a scholar.

391
00:32:12,463 --> 00:32:15,523
Perhaps a priest,
a man of the people.

392
00:32:16,734 --> 00:32:19,168
Remember you are a Luna.
And a Marez.

393
00:32:19,537 --> 00:32:22,938
Deborah, take him
to Miss Maestas.

394
00:32:23,274 --> 00:32:25,139
She knows my family.
Sí, Mama.

395
00:32:28,513 --> 00:32:29,605
My scholar.

396
00:32:29,714 --> 00:32:31,682
Ooh! A scholar already,

397
00:32:32,383 --> 00:32:35,079
and only on your first day
of school, mijo? (CHUCKLES)

398
00:32:35,153 --> 00:32:37,713
You know, in my day only the
rich got to go to school.

399
00:32:38,389 --> 00:32:41,324
My father, he gave me a saddle
blanket and a wild pony,

400
00:32:41,392 --> 00:32:45,089
and he said, "There, the
llano, there's your life."

401
00:32:45,663 --> 00:32:48,530
Ves, mijito?
That's why we live here,

402
00:32:48,599 --> 00:32:52,091
on this dry piece of dirt
where nothing grows,

403
00:32:52,470 --> 00:32:56,372
so your father can be close
to his old Marez ways.

404
00:32:56,574 --> 00:32:58,041
Mijo, why don't you
ask your mom,

405
00:32:58,109 --> 00:32:59,838
what was it that made her
fall in love with me, huh?

406
00:32:59,911 --> 00:33:02,778
Was the sweat of the horse
in my clothes,

407
00:33:02,847 --> 00:33:06,180
or its smell on my hands that
made her fall so in love with me?

408
00:33:06,250 --> 00:33:09,151
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

409
00:33:09,220 --> 00:33:10,312
DEBORAH:
Time to go, Mama.

410
00:33:10,388 --> 00:33:12,652
Yes, it's time to go.
Yeah, so it is.

411
00:33:13,291 --> 00:33:14,519
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

412
00:33:15,393 --> 00:33:16,655
Theresa?

413
00:33:19,564 --> 00:33:23,796
Mis hijos! All right. Remember,
be respectful to your teachers.

414
00:33:24,402 --> 00:33:26,563
And Antonio, suerte.

415
00:33:29,807 --> 00:33:31,104
Go, go, go, go, go.

416
00:33:31,175 --> 00:33:33,405
Give Miss Maestas
my blessings, hmm?

417
00:33:46,858 --> 00:33:48,189
(SCREECHING)

418
00:33:55,533 --> 00:33:56,966
(BOY SCREAMING)

419
00:33:57,035 --> 00:33:58,900
Vitamin Kid!
Who?

420
00:34:02,807 --> 00:34:04,274
(GREETING IN SPANISH)

421
00:34:12,450 --> 00:34:13,644
(EXHALES)

422
00:34:22,126 --> 00:34:24,151
Your classroom's over there!

423
00:34:39,944 --> 00:34:42,105
Good morning!
Como te llamas?

424
00:34:42,246 --> 00:34:43,611
Antonio Marez.

425
00:34:45,149 --> 00:34:47,242
My mother said
to send you her blessings.

426
00:34:47,885 --> 00:34:48,943
Hmm.

427
00:34:49,387 --> 00:34:52,049
"Antonio Marez."

428
00:34:58,062 --> 00:35:00,826
You wanna learn to write?
(AGREES IN SPANISH)

429
00:35:01,232 --> 00:35:05,931
Good, come in. Let's put
you next to Melissa.

430
00:35:07,405 --> 00:35:09,396
Melissa, this is Antonio.

431
00:35:10,808 --> 00:35:12,503
(CLEARING THROAT) Up!

432
00:35:15,813 --> 00:35:17,144
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

433
00:35:18,850 --> 00:35:21,717
Attention, class,
it's lunchtime.

434
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:24,554
You'll obey Marisol
until I return.

435
00:35:39,537 --> 00:35:40,970
(GIGGLING)

436
00:35:42,874 --> 00:35:44,102
(GIRL LAUGHING)

437
00:35:45,209 --> 00:35:47,268
(ALL LAUGHING)

438
00:36:41,966 --> 00:36:45,402
This is cardo lechero,
good for cleansing the liver.

439
00:36:45,469 --> 00:36:47,232
We have some in the house.

440
00:36:48,272 --> 00:36:51,708
Ah, mira, this...
This is marrubio

441
00:36:52,076 --> 00:36:53,600
for when you have a cold.

442
00:36:53,711 --> 00:36:55,838
You can make candy with that.

443
00:37:13,864 --> 00:37:15,957
ULTIMA: Antonio!

444
00:37:18,302 --> 00:37:20,293
Antonio!

445
00:37:35,553 --> 00:37:37,817
Andrew! Leon! Eugene!

446
00:37:38,155 --> 00:37:41,716
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

447
00:37:48,899 --> 00:37:50,059
(SCREAMS)

448
00:37:51,736 --> 00:37:52,964
(LAUGHING)

449
00:37:56,240 --> 00:37:57,400
Mama!

450
00:37:58,509 --> 00:38:01,410
Hola! Hola, Papa!

451
00:38:12,623 --> 00:38:14,056
(CHUCKLING)

452
00:38:14,125 --> 00:38:15,820
So, tell me
all about California.

453
00:38:15,893 --> 00:38:17,326
Well, we were only there
a few months, Papa.

454
00:38:17,461 --> 00:38:19,361
Tell us about the war!

455
00:38:21,065 --> 00:38:22,396
It was all right.

456
00:38:22,500 --> 00:38:23,660
Like heck, it was!

457
00:38:23,734 --> 00:38:25,326
Eugene, shame!

458
00:38:25,603 --> 00:38:27,195
In front of La Grande!

459
00:38:27,405 --> 00:38:28,872
Did you see
all the vineyards, huh?

460
00:38:29,173 --> 00:38:33,667
Ay, Dios mio. It was
so hard without you.

461
00:38:34,011 --> 00:38:35,171
It'll be all right now, Mama.

462
00:38:35,246 --> 00:38:36,304
Híjole! You know,

463
00:38:36,380 --> 00:38:39,178
I would give anything to move
to California right now!

464
00:38:39,417 --> 00:38:42,443
Gabriel...
They've just returned.

465
00:38:42,753 --> 00:38:44,448
Ay, mi amor,
I don't mean tonight.

466
00:38:49,493 --> 00:38:50,824
Mis hijos.

467
00:38:51,595 --> 00:38:54,996
Do you get to punch
the buttons on the, um...

468
00:38:55,066 --> 00:38:56,863
ANDREW: Cash register?
Yeah.

469
00:38:57,001 --> 00:38:58,195
That'll come later.

470
00:38:58,269 --> 00:39:00,669
For now I work
mostly in the back.

471
00:39:01,739 --> 00:39:02,831
Gotten any faster?

472
00:39:04,108 --> 00:39:05,769
Think you could beat me?

473
00:39:06,410 --> 00:39:07,707
Race you across!

474
00:39:09,013 --> 00:39:10,708
(CHUCKLES)

475
00:39:14,885 --> 00:39:17,217
It's him, the Vitamin Kid!
Let's go!

476
00:39:17,655 --> 00:39:18,986
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

477
00:39:21,792 --> 00:39:23,487
(ALL PANTING)

478
00:39:25,363 --> 00:39:27,957
Ah, who the heck was that?

479
00:39:29,033 --> 00:39:32,799
The Vitamin Kid.
Nobody could beat him.

480
00:39:34,071 --> 00:39:36,835
Some day you'll beat him,
Tony. Some day.

481
00:39:38,376 --> 00:39:40,139
(SIGHS) See you after work.

482
00:39:44,749 --> 00:39:46,512
What is sin, anyway?

483
00:39:46,584 --> 00:39:48,814
It's not doing the will of God.

484
00:39:48,953 --> 00:39:51,251
Is it a sin to do this? Yes.

485
00:39:52,256 --> 00:39:54,190
Why?
It's a bad sign.

486
00:39:54,592 --> 00:39:56,082
But nothing happens
when I do it.

487
00:39:56,193 --> 00:39:57,353
You will be punished.

488
00:39:57,461 --> 00:39:58,894
When?
When you die.

489
00:39:59,630 --> 00:40:00,892
What if I go to confession?

490
00:40:00,998 --> 00:40:03,091
Then your sins are forgiven,

491
00:40:03,167 --> 00:40:05,658
your soul is clean
and you're saved.

492
00:40:06,103 --> 00:40:07,968
You mean I can go out and sin,

493
00:40:08,072 --> 00:40:10,370
throw the finger,
say bad words,

494
00:40:10,441 --> 00:40:12,341
steal, do a million bad things,

495
00:40:12,443 --> 00:40:14,240
and when I'm about to die,

496
00:40:14,311 --> 00:40:16,279
just go to confession
and I go to heaven?

497
00:40:16,347 --> 00:40:18,679
Yes, if you're
sorry you sinned.

498
00:40:18,749 --> 00:40:20,808
(SCREAMING)
(GRUNTS)

499
00:40:21,318 --> 00:40:23,081
Hey, Tony, you missed a fight.

500
00:40:23,521 --> 00:40:25,580
That was a real
good tackle, Horse.

501
00:40:26,257 --> 00:40:27,747
Now let me up.

502
00:40:30,027 --> 00:40:32,052
Did you see the fight?

503
00:40:32,129 --> 00:40:35,929
It was funny when Willie
peed on Roque's shoes.

504
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:37,160
Oh, yeah.

505
00:40:37,301 --> 00:40:39,792
Hey, how come Willie
and those farmer kids

506
00:40:39,870 --> 00:40:41,394
don't have to go to catechism?

507
00:40:41,539 --> 00:40:43,439
'Cause they'd miss
the bus, stupid!

508
00:40:43,707 --> 00:40:45,607
Protestants don't
have to go either.

509
00:40:45,709 --> 00:40:46,937
They go to Hell!

510
00:40:47,378 --> 00:40:48,777
No, they don't!

511
00:40:48,913 --> 00:40:50,642
You're going to
Hell too, Florence.

512
00:40:50,714 --> 00:40:52,147
You don't believe in God.

513
00:40:52,216 --> 00:40:54,480
If you don't believe in God,
there's no Hell to go to.

514
00:40:54,618 --> 00:40:56,711
Hey, let's go tease the girls.

515
00:41:00,124 --> 00:41:02,285
Why don't you believe in God?

516
00:41:03,160 --> 00:41:06,095
I don't know. My mother
died when I was three.

517
00:41:09,633 --> 00:41:12,067
My father drinks
himself to death,

518
00:41:13,838 --> 00:41:16,568
and my sisters are
floozies working at Rosie's.

519
00:41:18,209 --> 00:41:20,040
The old man hasn't been
very good to me.

520
00:41:20,411 --> 00:41:21,935
You mean God?

521
00:41:22,413 --> 00:41:24,711
So why do you
go to catechism then?

522
00:41:25,483 --> 00:41:26,916
I wanna be with you guys.

523
00:41:27,351 --> 00:41:30,081
You know, I don't
want to be left out.

524
00:41:31,622 --> 00:41:32,953
(CHURCH BELL TOLLING)

525
00:41:33,023 --> 00:41:34,354
We're gonna be late.

526
00:41:56,680 --> 00:41:58,477
I would not have
expected you to be late.

527
00:41:59,216 --> 00:42:02,083
I'll excuse you this time,
but take care of your company.

528
00:42:02,720 --> 00:42:05,348
The devil has many ways
to mislead you.

529
00:42:12,763 --> 00:42:14,924
You think this kind of
disrespect can be tolerated?

530
00:42:14,999 --> 00:42:16,432
You think this is play time?

531
00:42:16,734 --> 00:42:18,201
Let us pray.

532
00:42:29,513 --> 00:42:31,640
(SAYING THE LORD'S PRAYER
IN SPANISH)

533
00:42:36,320 --> 00:42:37,446
FATHER BYRNE:
Who made you?

534
00:42:37,521 --> 00:42:40,319
CHILDREN: God made me.

535
00:42:41,492 --> 00:42:43,653
And where is God?

536
00:42:43,761 --> 00:42:46,355
CHILDREN:
God is everywhere.

537
00:42:46,497 --> 00:42:47,828
(WHISPERS) At Rosie's.

538
00:42:47,898 --> 00:42:49,991
How many persons
are there in God?

539
00:42:50,067 --> 00:42:51,534
ALL: Three!

540
00:42:51,702 --> 00:42:55,661
The Father, the Son
and the Holy Ghost.

541
00:42:55,739 --> 00:42:57,639
They have to squeeze in tight.

542
00:42:57,708 --> 00:43:00,677
If you die with a mortal
sin on your head,

543
00:43:01,679 --> 00:43:03,704
where do you go?
Hell!

544
00:43:06,016 --> 00:43:08,041
And is there
any escape from Hell?

545
00:43:08,285 --> 00:43:10,310
ALL: No!
FATHER BYRNE: No.

546
00:43:11,422 --> 00:43:14,949
You burn in Hell forever.

547
00:43:16,160 --> 00:43:17,821
For eternity.

548
00:43:19,029 --> 00:43:21,691
How long is eternity?
Without end.

549
00:43:21,899 --> 00:43:23,366
Twenty years.
(SMIRKING)

550
00:43:39,216 --> 00:43:40,808
(ALL LAUGHING)

551
00:43:44,888 --> 00:43:46,082
FATHER BYRNE:
That is enough.

552
00:43:49,760 --> 00:43:52,627
ADULT ANTONIO: The dark buds of
spring were on the branches.

553
00:43:52,763 --> 00:43:55,493
And I understood why they
called the raging sap

554
00:43:55,566 --> 00:43:58,364
that brought forth life,
the bad blood.

555
00:43:59,203 --> 00:44:01,034
Now it ran through my brothers.

556
00:44:02,206 --> 00:44:03,434
There were whispers in town

557
00:44:03,507 --> 00:44:06,374
that they were wasting their
service money at the bars,

558
00:44:06,443 --> 00:44:09,310
pool halls,
and even at Rosie's.

559
00:44:09,813 --> 00:44:11,644
(GOAT BLEATING)

560
00:44:33,771 --> 00:44:36,137
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

561
00:44:36,206 --> 00:44:38,538
(GABRIEL SHOUTING) EUGENE: When
are we supposed to come to you?

562
00:44:38,609 --> 00:44:40,406
When are we supposed
to come to you?

563
00:44:40,477 --> 00:44:42,741
GABRIEL: That's not
what I'm talking about!

564
00:44:42,813 --> 00:44:44,474
I said, I'm working
days and nights.

565
00:44:44,548 --> 00:44:46,106
EUGENE: And we're not working?
GABRIEL: No, you're not!

566
00:44:46,183 --> 00:44:49,584
We're not working, huh?
What's this about?

567
00:44:49,653 --> 00:44:52,417
GABRIEL: Now I'm trying to keep
you guys in line. I have work!

568
00:44:52,556 --> 00:44:54,854
EUGENE: What kind of work
can you have for us here?

569
00:44:54,925 --> 00:44:56,153
GABRIEL: I have
jobs lined up!

570
00:44:56,226 --> 00:44:57,986
You are going to work
with me on the highway!

571
00:44:58,028 --> 00:44:59,948
We don't wanna work with
you on the darn highway!

572
00:44:59,963 --> 00:45:02,090
Eugenio!
Watch your language!

573
00:45:02,166 --> 00:45:03,258
Do not defy your father.

574
00:45:03,534 --> 00:45:05,627
I'm not defying my father, Mama.
That's enough!

575
00:45:06,570 --> 00:45:08,902
EUGENE: Perdoname, Mama.
MARIA: Perdoname, Mama.

576
00:45:09,139 --> 00:45:10,436
(EUGENE SPEAKING SPANISH)

577
00:45:10,507 --> 00:45:12,839
What is it you want? Eh?

578
00:45:14,211 --> 00:45:15,735
You've been gone so long,

579
00:45:15,813 --> 00:45:19,180
and now that you've returned
you want to leave again?

580
00:45:20,117 --> 00:45:22,677
What about California? EUGENE:
What about California?

581
00:45:24,788 --> 00:45:26,779
We don't wanna
go to California.

582
00:45:28,492 --> 00:45:31,120
We wanna be on our own
and make our own way.

583
00:45:31,762 --> 00:45:33,252
Go to Santa Fe and work.

584
00:45:33,764 --> 00:45:35,288
You are forsaking me.

585
00:45:37,768 --> 00:45:39,702
We're not forsaking you, Mama.

586
00:45:39,770 --> 00:45:41,761
EUGENE: Mama! We're men.

587
00:45:43,540 --> 00:45:45,201
We have seen the world.

588
00:45:45,843 --> 00:45:47,743
MARIA: Ay, Marez men.

589
00:45:48,612 --> 00:45:51,945
The Marez blood draws
them away from their home

590
00:45:54,451 --> 00:45:56,510
and their parents, Gabriel.

591
00:46:03,794 --> 00:46:05,284
You still have Tony.

592
00:46:06,396 --> 00:46:07,886
Thanks be to God.

593
00:46:29,787 --> 00:46:31,846
You're not going with them?

594
00:46:34,525 --> 00:46:36,152
I got a job here.

595
00:46:37,427 --> 00:46:38,792
Figure I could do as well here

596
00:46:38,896 --> 00:46:41,956
as they do in Santa Fe
or Albuquerque.

597
00:46:44,168 --> 00:46:45,931
Will you miss them?

598
00:46:50,073 --> 00:46:51,370
Sure.

599
00:46:52,075 --> 00:46:53,372
Me too.

600
00:46:59,349 --> 00:47:02,807
Will you become a
farmer like Mama wants?

601
00:47:04,955 --> 00:47:06,320
No.

602
00:47:08,258 --> 00:47:09,748
Will you become a priest?

603
00:47:12,062 --> 00:47:13,290
(SCOFFS)

604
00:47:25,709 --> 00:47:26,937
Thank you.

605
00:47:31,849 --> 00:47:35,410
Okay, everyone,
class is dismissed.

606
00:47:38,956 --> 00:47:40,355
Have a great summer.

607
00:47:42,292 --> 00:47:44,556
Hold... Hold on,
Antonio, hold on.

608
00:47:48,232 --> 00:47:50,928
Bye, Miss Maestas. Bye-bye.
Thank you so much.

609
00:47:51,001 --> 00:47:52,969
Goodbye, boys.
Thank you.

610
00:47:56,506 --> 00:48:00,033
Antonio, you're a little older
than most of the other kids.

611
00:48:00,143 --> 00:48:01,940
And your progress
has been very good.

612
00:48:02,045 --> 00:48:05,310
So, instead of passing you
to the second grade,

613
00:48:05,916 --> 00:48:07,577
we're passing you to the third.

614
00:48:09,453 --> 00:48:11,944
Gracias. I mean, thank
you, Miss Maestas.

615
00:48:12,022 --> 00:48:15,423
(LAUGHS) Have a good summer, Antonio.
Y, suerte.

616
00:48:16,960 --> 00:48:18,655
I'll see you next year,
Miss Maestas!

617
00:48:18,729 --> 00:48:20,253
Yes, you will.

618
00:48:23,300 --> 00:48:24,961
Hey, Tony!

619
00:48:26,270 --> 00:48:28,636
Pass?
Yeah.

620
00:48:28,772 --> 00:48:30,706
Come on, let's go!

621
00:48:40,350 --> 00:48:42,215
One of them
has started melting.

622
00:48:42,886 --> 00:48:44,285
(ULTIMA ASKING IN SPANISH)

623
00:48:44,488 --> 00:48:45,785
The doll.

624
00:48:52,763 --> 00:48:54,253
Don't touch it.

625
00:49:03,073 --> 00:49:04,836
(PANTING)

626
00:49:05,943 --> 00:49:07,240
(BANGING ON DOOR)

627
00:49:08,045 --> 00:49:10,275
(SPEAKING SPANISH) Tenorio.

628
00:49:10,447 --> 00:49:12,472
(ENQUIRING IN SPANISH) Tenorio.

629
00:49:12,783 --> 00:49:14,683
He's drunk! NARCISO:
No, I'm not drunk!

630
00:49:15,419 --> 00:49:17,353
Grande, you must hide!

631
00:49:17,421 --> 00:49:19,446
Hombre! Hombre,
make sense!

632
00:49:19,690 --> 00:49:22,386
Maria, put the children
in the other room.

633
00:49:22,459 --> 00:49:23,926
Why do I have to hide?

634
00:49:24,061 --> 00:49:25,187
NARCISO:
Have you not heard?

635
00:49:25,262 --> 00:49:26,343
GABRIEL:
Heard what, hombre?

636
00:49:26,396 --> 00:49:29,490
Ay, Dios mio, living on this
cursed hill away from town.

637
00:49:30,434 --> 00:49:34,598
Today Tenorio's daughter,
his witch, died.

638
00:49:35,072 --> 00:49:37,063
He blames La Grande for it.

639
00:49:37,174 --> 00:49:38,607
(MARIA EXCLAIMS IN SPANISH)

640
00:49:41,111 --> 00:49:42,510
Who told you this story?

641
00:49:42,746 --> 00:49:44,543
Jesus Silva
came from El Puerto.

642
00:49:44,614 --> 00:49:47,014
He said that Tenorio filled
some men with whiskey

643
00:49:47,084 --> 00:49:48,915
and had them
spread his vengeance.

644
00:49:49,019 --> 00:49:50,499
(MEN SHOUTING IN DISTANCE)
Oh, my God!

645
00:49:55,826 --> 00:49:58,386
(MEN CLAMORING)

646
00:50:07,104 --> 00:50:08,765
Wait here.

647
00:50:08,872 --> 00:50:12,069
Papa!
Antonio! Antonio!

648
00:50:13,810 --> 00:50:16,005
(SPEAKING SPANISH)
Antonio, you stay there!

649
00:50:18,415 --> 00:50:19,746
Stay!

650
00:50:23,587 --> 00:50:24,781
MAN: Gabriel Marez!

651
00:50:29,559 --> 00:50:30,753
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

652
00:50:30,994 --> 00:50:33,485
We don't wanna
quarrel with you, Marez!

653
00:50:33,563 --> 00:50:34,996
We only want the witch.

654
00:50:35,132 --> 00:50:36,497
Who speaks?

655
00:50:40,404 --> 00:50:41,803
Come, come.

656
00:50:42,773 --> 00:50:45,503
You call me by my name!
You walk on my land!

657
00:50:46,376 --> 00:50:48,139
I wanna know who speaks!

658
00:50:50,213 --> 00:50:52,909
TENORIO: Our business here
tonight is not with you, Marez.

659
00:50:53,517 --> 00:50:54,984
GABRIEL: You walk
upon my land!

660
00:50:55,252 --> 00:50:56,514
That is my business!

661
00:50:56,586 --> 00:50:58,417
TENORIO: We do not want
to quarrel with you.

662
00:50:58,488 --> 00:51:00,786
MAN: We only want the witch!
Just give her to us.

663
00:51:01,091 --> 00:51:04,185
We'll take her away
and there'll be no trouble.

664
00:51:09,066 --> 00:51:10,294
Who accuses her?

665
00:51:10,534 --> 00:51:13,332
I, Tenorio Trementina!

666
00:51:17,007 --> 00:51:19,737
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

667
00:51:20,410 --> 00:51:23,402
And, you are idiota
with nothing but...

668
00:51:23,547 --> 00:51:24,809
(ALL CLAMORING)

669
00:51:25,916 --> 00:51:28,043
Wait! Wait, Marez!

670
00:51:28,552 --> 00:51:30,383
We're not here to fight you.

671
00:51:30,454 --> 00:51:34,356
There's not a man here, not one,
that doesn't hold you in respect.

672
00:51:34,624 --> 00:51:35,921
You know that.

673
00:51:36,126 --> 00:51:38,253
Pero, esta brujería,
this witchcraft,

674
00:51:38,528 --> 00:51:39,995
it's serious business, hombre,

675
00:51:40,130 --> 00:51:41,995
and the charges
must be answered!

676
00:51:42,732 --> 00:51:44,962
Give us the witch!
There's no witch here.

677
00:51:45,102 --> 00:51:47,182
ALL: (CHANTING) Give us the witch!
Give us the witch!

678
00:51:47,838 --> 00:51:49,430
(CLAMORING)

679
00:51:54,444 --> 00:51:55,638
Get away!

680
00:51:55,712 --> 00:51:56,912
(NARCISO ENQUIRING IN SPANISH)

681
00:51:58,715 --> 00:52:03,414
Why are farmers out playing
vigilantes when they should be home

682
00:52:04,321 --> 00:52:07,722
sitting by a warm fire,
playing cards?

683
00:52:09,292 --> 00:52:13,991
I know you're not men who need the
cover of darkness to hide behind.

684
00:52:15,332 --> 00:52:20,998
You shame your good names by
following este idiota de Tenorio!

685
00:52:22,105 --> 00:52:24,198
He has lost his daughter today,

686
00:52:24,274 --> 00:52:26,742
and for that El Puerto
can sleep easier,

687
00:52:26,810 --> 00:52:30,302
now that her evil doing
has gone to heck with her!

688
00:52:30,380 --> 00:52:32,075
(CUSSING IN SPANISH)

689
00:52:36,953 --> 00:52:40,616
I may be a beast,
but I am not a fool.

690
00:52:41,024 --> 00:52:43,492
He calls you fools.
Enough of this talking!

691
00:52:43,693 --> 00:52:45,126
We came here for the witch!

692
00:52:45,195 --> 00:52:46,219
Give us the witch!

693
00:52:46,530 --> 00:52:47,622
Give us the bruja!

694
00:52:47,697 --> 00:52:49,289
Wait!

695
00:52:49,633 --> 00:52:52,329
You know the simple test
for a witch.

696
00:52:54,704 --> 00:52:56,001
Are these needles holy?

697
00:52:57,440 --> 00:52:59,032
Sí. Blessed by the priest.

698
00:52:59,676 --> 00:53:02,008
Take the holy needles
and pin them to the door.

699
00:53:02,078 --> 00:53:04,740
No, no, no, no, no.

700
00:53:05,282 --> 00:53:06,943
MAN: Just give us the witch!

701
00:53:07,150 --> 00:53:09,482
Put them in
so they are crossed.

702
00:53:09,719 --> 00:53:11,380
In the name of God, you'll know

703
00:53:11,454 --> 00:53:13,945
that a witch cannot
walk through a door

704
00:53:14,024 --> 00:53:16,151
so marked by the sign
of the Christ!

705
00:53:16,893 --> 00:53:18,588
CRUZ: It's true!
It's legal in our customs!

706
00:53:20,530 --> 00:53:22,725
NARCISO: But we all must
abide by the trial!

707
00:53:24,534 --> 00:53:26,525
I'll abide by that test!

708
00:53:30,340 --> 00:53:32,706
I'll abide.
But if she crosses it,

709
00:53:33,210 --> 00:53:36,304
then she can never again
be accused for witchcraft!

710
00:53:36,846 --> 00:53:38,905
We call God as our witness!

711
00:53:41,451 --> 00:53:43,248
Who is it accuses me?

712
00:53:44,221 --> 00:53:47,782
I accuse you of being a witch!

713
00:53:48,024 --> 00:53:49,286
(OWL SCREECHES)

714
00:53:50,360 --> 00:53:51,952
(MEN YELLING)

715
00:53:52,495 --> 00:53:53,894
(MEN YELLING IN SPANISH)

716
00:53:55,298 --> 00:53:56,560
(SCREECHING)
(SCREAMING)

717
00:54:06,543 --> 00:54:08,670
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

718
00:54:12,782 --> 00:54:14,215
It's proven!

719
00:54:15,819 --> 00:54:16,945
It's proven.

720
00:54:17,120 --> 00:54:19,611
Her evil bird has blinded me!

721
00:54:20,857 --> 00:54:22,222
I curse you, bruja!

722
00:54:23,193 --> 00:54:26,754
Grande, come inside. TENORIO: Don't you see?
She's a bruja!

723
00:54:27,364 --> 00:54:31,391
Narciso, I swear,
you'll pay for this!

724
00:54:32,035 --> 00:54:34,367
I will see you dead!

725
00:54:40,510 --> 00:54:43,172
Híjole.
What a night, huh?

726
00:54:45,482 --> 00:54:47,746
Come on, my old friend.

727
00:54:47,817 --> 00:54:49,182
I could use a drink.

728
00:55:20,784 --> 00:55:22,183
(BIDDING FAREWELL) Bye.

729
00:55:23,586 --> 00:55:25,850
Send my love to Grandpa,

730
00:55:25,922 --> 00:55:28,755
and tell Mateo
he's still a lousy pitcher.

731
00:55:32,195 --> 00:55:35,426
(SPEAKING SPANISH)
(AGREES IN SPANISH)

732
00:55:51,781 --> 00:55:53,305
(WOMAN SPEAKING SPANISH)

733
00:55:53,750 --> 00:55:56,218
Do you believe that God
will burn all the sinners

734
00:55:56,286 --> 00:55:58,550
forever and ever when they die?

735
00:55:59,122 --> 00:56:00,180
(AGREES IN SPANISH)

736
00:56:03,626 --> 00:56:07,619
Do you think if God was a
woman, she would forgive them?

737
00:56:08,298 --> 00:56:12,325
Like the Virgin Mary, she forgave
the people who killed her son.

738
00:56:14,371 --> 00:56:16,305
I don't know, Antonio.

739
00:56:20,877 --> 00:56:23,710
Why didn't you come
to warn us last night?

740
00:56:29,452 --> 00:56:33,354
Well, your grandfather
wouldn't let us mix

741
00:56:33,423 --> 00:56:35,550
in what took place yesterday.

742
00:56:36,493 --> 00:56:38,723
But, Ultima cured Uncle Lucas.

743
00:56:39,729 --> 00:56:41,128
Isn't he grateful for that?

744
00:56:41,498 --> 00:56:43,090
Of course he is.

745
00:56:43,733 --> 00:56:45,826
(SIGHING) You just
don't understand.

746
00:56:46,636 --> 00:56:47,694
What?

747
00:56:49,172 --> 00:56:51,470
El Puerto,
it's a small village.

748
00:56:52,108 --> 00:56:54,542
We've lived there
for a long time.

749
00:56:54,844 --> 00:56:56,368
We've never passed
judgment on anyone.

750
00:56:57,614 --> 00:57:00,515
But you let Tenorio
pass judgment on Ultima.

751
00:57:10,693 --> 00:57:12,320
(HORSE NEIGHING)

752
00:57:26,042 --> 00:57:29,671
ADULT ANTONIO: The end of summer
was the time of the harvest.

753
00:57:32,582 --> 00:57:35,915
My mother's family
had always been farmers

754
00:57:35,985 --> 00:57:38,613
who took their only truth
from the earth.

755
00:57:39,022 --> 00:57:41,752
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

756
00:57:41,825 --> 00:57:46,285
The chilis, corn and fruit that
would carry us through the winter,

757
00:57:47,397 --> 00:57:51,026
they saw as sacred gifts from
the ground beneath our feet.

758
00:57:57,173 --> 00:57:59,300
The harvest of my grandfather's

759
00:57:59,375 --> 00:58:01,070
was my favorite time of year.

760
00:58:02,879 --> 00:58:03,971
(MEN LAUGHING)

761
00:58:04,047 --> 00:58:05,344
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

762
00:58:07,317 --> 00:58:08,648
Okay, Papa.

763
