1020
01:17:49,297 --> 01:17:50,855
he swore he would kill you.

1021
01:17:51,767 --> 01:17:53,667
Don't worry about Tenorio.

1022
01:17:55,003 --> 01:17:56,595
He's just an old wolf

1023
01:17:56,672 --> 01:17:59,869
who drags around the ground
where he made his kill.

1024
01:18:00,842 --> 01:18:03,174
His conscience
will not let him sleep.

1025
01:18:03,512 --> 01:18:06,140
But where there is no penance,

1026
01:18:07,816 --> 01:18:09,943
there can be no forgiveness.

1027
01:18:27,002 --> 01:18:28,333
(DOOR OPENS)

1028
01:18:29,471 --> 01:18:31,234
The door's opening!

1029
01:18:35,977 --> 01:18:37,945
It's a big day, Antonito.

1030
01:18:56,565 --> 01:18:58,089
Florence said the blood is wine

1031
01:18:58,166 --> 01:18:59,690
because the priest is a wino.

1032
01:18:59,868 --> 01:19:00,857
(CHUCKLING)

1033
01:19:00,936 --> 01:19:02,369
Oh, my God,

1034
01:19:03,505 --> 01:19:05,200
I'm sorry for all my sins...

1035
01:19:05,741 --> 01:19:08,175
(SHUSHING) All good
and deserving...

1036
01:19:15,317 --> 01:19:17,478
FATHER BYRNE: Corpus Christi.
Amen.

1037
01:19:21,556 --> 01:19:23,683
FATHER BYRNE: Corpus Christi.
BOY: Amen.

1038
01:19:25,393 --> 01:19:28,328
Corpus Christi.
(GAGGING)

1039
01:19:32,033 --> 01:19:33,432
Corpus Christi.

1040
01:19:33,802 --> 01:19:35,030
Amen.

1041
01:19:37,139 --> 01:19:38,629
(CONTINUES GAGGING)

1042
01:19:46,982 --> 01:19:49,610
Tony! Tony! Go on,
you're holding up the line.

1043
01:19:52,053 --> 01:19:53,850
Dummy! You got us
all mixed up!

1044
01:19:54,556 --> 01:19:56,490
Darn!
I almost choked.

1045
01:19:58,126 --> 01:20:00,253
Do you feel anything?
I feel hungry.

1046
01:20:07,068 --> 01:20:08,092
(SIGHING)

1047
01:20:08,170 --> 01:20:10,331
ADULT ANTONIO: Now that
I was one with God,

1048
01:20:10,405 --> 01:20:13,966
I would ask him why Tenorio
was alive instead of Narciso?

1049
01:20:16,111 --> 01:20:18,773
Why he had allowed evil
to happen?

1050
01:20:18,847 --> 01:20:20,781
Why it went unpunished?

1051
01:20:21,950 --> 01:20:25,147
I called out to him
that now was a part of me.

1052
01:20:27,022 --> 01:20:28,922
Go in peace with Christ.

1053
01:20:28,990 --> 01:20:31,254
CONGREGATION:
Thanks be to God.

1054
01:20:34,963 --> 01:20:37,591
ADULT ANTONIO:
But there was no answer.

1055
01:20:37,866 --> 01:20:40,357
In time,
everyone got up to leave.

1056
01:20:42,537 --> 01:20:43,970
It was over.

1057
01:20:55,150 --> 01:20:56,981
(SPEAKING SPANISH)
(FARMER SPEAKING SPANISH)

1058
01:20:59,221 --> 01:21:00,381
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1059
01:21:00,455 --> 01:21:03,583
ADULT ANTONIO: After Communion, I
spent more and more time with Ultima

1060
01:21:03,658 --> 01:21:06,092
whose wisdom gave me comfort.

1061
01:21:06,161 --> 01:21:10,530
I learned that the ways of healing
attended more than just the body.

1062
01:21:10,599 --> 01:21:14,330
And no road was too long for her
to travel to ease someone's pain,

1063
01:21:14,402 --> 01:21:16,893
or to lift a curse,
or cool a fever.

1064
01:21:17,839 --> 01:21:19,966
But often when
their miseries passed,

1065
01:21:20,041 --> 01:21:22,305
they shunned her just the same.

1066
01:21:33,588 --> 01:21:35,021
What'll you do this summer?

1067
01:21:36,258 --> 01:21:37,520
I don't know.

1068
01:21:38,860 --> 01:21:39,986
Play.

1069
01:21:40,829 --> 01:21:41,955
Fish.

1070
01:21:43,231 --> 01:21:44,789
Take care of my animals.

1071
01:21:46,134 --> 01:21:49,001
Go to El Puerto to learn about
farming from my uncles.

1072
01:21:49,404 --> 01:21:50,769
Do you wanna be a farmer?

1073
01:21:51,273 --> 01:21:52,763
I don't know.

1074
01:21:53,942 --> 01:21:57,708
Ultima says a man's destiny must
unfold itself like a flower.

1075
01:21:58,647 --> 01:22:01,878
With only the sun, earth,

1076
01:22:01,950 --> 01:22:03,577
and water making it blossom,

1077
01:22:03,985 --> 01:22:06,545
and no one else meddling in it.

1078
01:22:09,157 --> 01:22:11,489
She sounds like
a very wise woman.

1079
01:22:12,227 --> 01:22:13,319
Yes.

1080
01:22:16,531 --> 01:22:18,328
Goodbye, Miss Violet.

1081
01:22:18,867 --> 01:22:20,960
I'll come by
to see you next year.

1082
01:22:21,036 --> 01:22:22,663
Goodbye, Antonio.

1083
01:22:48,496 --> 01:22:50,225
(YELLING) Race!

1084
01:23:16,091 --> 01:23:18,582
You know that there are
hidden lakes in those hills?

1085
01:23:18,660 --> 01:23:21,151
You know, with mermaids
in them, right?

1086
01:23:21,229 --> 01:23:24,426
And they call you,
and you go to them,

1087
01:23:25,834 --> 01:23:27,859
but no one ever sees you again.

1088
01:23:27,936 --> 01:23:30,370
BOY 1: (YELLING)
I can't see him!

1089
01:23:30,438 --> 01:23:31,803
BOY 2: He's been down there
way too long!

1090
01:23:31,906 --> 01:23:34,204
They're not supposed to be there!
Something is wrong.

1091
01:23:34,809 --> 01:23:36,470
Hurry!
MAN: Where is he?

1092
01:23:36,778 --> 01:23:37,870
ABEL: He's under!

1093
01:23:39,147 --> 01:23:40,978
Hurry up!

1094
01:23:41,049 --> 01:23:43,279
What happened? It's
Florence, he's down there!

1095
01:23:43,418 --> 01:23:44,476
Bones dared him to go in!

1096
01:23:44,552 --> 01:23:45,576
He didn't come up.

1097
01:23:45,653 --> 01:23:46,642
Look!

1098
01:24:13,381 --> 01:24:14,861
MAN: I told you kids
not to swim here.

1099
01:24:17,485 --> 01:24:19,009
(SOBBING)

1100
01:24:24,359 --> 01:24:25,519
(CHURCH BELL TOLLING)

1101
01:24:25,593 --> 01:24:28,460
ADULT ANTONIO: Florence
died without confession,

1102
01:24:28,530 --> 01:24:30,555
without the grace of God.

1103
01:24:31,099 --> 01:24:34,830
Alone in death
as he had been in life.

1104
01:24:37,138 --> 01:24:39,333
Was he wandering in purgatory?

1105
01:24:40,742 --> 01:24:42,972
Would he burn forever in Hell?

1106
01:24:44,979 --> 01:24:48,915
I wondered if God was angry
with him for not believing.

1107
01:24:51,019 --> 01:24:55,820
But mostly I wondered,
if he even cared at all.

1108
01:25:02,063 --> 01:25:04,531
Tony!
Tony!

1109
01:25:05,333 --> 01:25:06,425
Tony!

1110
01:25:08,903 --> 01:25:09,892
Tony!

1111
01:25:10,138 --> 01:25:11,435
Antonio.

1112
01:25:12,407 --> 01:25:13,567
(GASPING)

1113
01:25:15,243 --> 01:25:16,574
It's all right.

1114
01:25:18,313 --> 01:25:19,575
It's all right.

1115
01:25:20,115 --> 01:25:24,950
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1116
01:25:25,120 --> 01:25:26,644
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1117
01:25:35,864 --> 01:25:37,923
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

1118
01:25:47,775 --> 01:25:50,266
MARIA: He feels
everything too much.

1119
01:25:51,312 --> 01:25:53,303
Maybe he's seen too much.

1120
01:25:53,948 --> 01:25:55,609
He needs to rest.

1121
01:25:57,051 --> 01:26:00,612
A visit to El Puerto
will do him good.

1122
01:26:07,395 --> 01:26:10,796
Women will take an hour saying
goodbye if you let 'em.

1123
01:26:20,875 --> 01:26:22,069
Papa?

1124
01:26:23,778 --> 01:26:25,268
Why is there evil in the world?

1125
01:26:25,847 --> 01:26:28,407
Ay, mijo, you have
so many questions.

1126
01:26:30,118 --> 01:26:31,949
Didn't the priest
talk about it in church?

1127
01:26:33,121 --> 01:26:35,089
But I'd like
to know your answer.

1128
01:26:36,724 --> 01:26:39,420
Oh... Oh, okay, well...

1129
01:26:41,162 --> 01:26:43,858
In that case, I'll
tell you how I see it.

1130
01:26:45,099 --> 01:26:48,694
I think most of the things we
call evil, aren't evil at all.

1131
01:26:48,770 --> 01:26:51,568
It's just that we don't
understand what they are,

1132
01:26:51,639 --> 01:26:53,038
so we call 'em evil.

1133
01:26:55,643 --> 01:26:57,702
Like, when Lucas, he...
He got sick,

1134
01:26:57,779 --> 01:26:59,178
and we were all afraid.

1135
01:26:59,581 --> 01:27:01,811
But Ultima, she wasn't afraid,

1136
01:27:01,883 --> 01:27:03,441
she understood what was wrong.

1137
01:27:03,718 --> 01:27:05,845
But, I took the Holy Communion

1138
01:27:05,920 --> 01:27:08,252
because I wanted to understand.

1139
01:27:09,591 --> 01:27:11,616
Understanding doesn't
come that easy, Tony.

1140
01:27:12,727 --> 01:27:14,558
Doesn't God give understanding?

1141
01:27:17,131 --> 01:27:18,428
(SIGHING)

1142
01:27:20,568 --> 01:27:22,126
Understanding comes with life.

1143
01:27:24,005 --> 01:27:27,941
As a man grows,
he sees life and death.

1144
01:27:29,110 --> 01:27:30,873
He's happy, he's sad, he works,

1145
01:27:30,945 --> 01:27:33,743
he plays, he meets people.

1146
01:27:35,583 --> 01:27:38,780
Sometimes it takes a whole
lifetime to acquire understanding.

1147
01:27:42,724 --> 01:27:46,125
But, mijo, in the end,

1148
01:27:46,995 --> 01:27:53,161
understanding simply means to have
sympathy, sympathy for people, yeah?

1149
01:27:53,501 --> 01:27:54,695
And Ultima...

1150
01:27:55,637 --> 01:27:57,229
Ultima has sympathy for people.

1151
01:27:58,306 --> 01:28:00,171
But with her, mijo,

1152
01:28:00,241 --> 01:28:04,735
with her it's so complete that she
can touch their souls and cure them.

1153
01:28:06,314 --> 01:28:09,249
That's her magic?
(AGREES IN SPANISH)

1154
01:28:09,984 --> 01:28:11,781
And in all this world

1155
01:28:12,687 --> 01:28:14,416
no greater magic can exist.

1156
01:28:17,725 --> 01:28:18,987
(CHUCKLES)

1157
01:28:24,966 --> 01:28:27,958
ADULT ANTONIO: All summer
I worked alongside my uncles.

1158
01:28:28,903 --> 01:28:33,363
I watched the care and the respect
they showed the earth and the plants.

1159
01:28:34,008 --> 01:28:38,342
Only Ultima showed such reverence
for the land and its offerings.

1160
01:28:39,781 --> 01:28:43,342
I learned that the phases of the
moon not only ruled the planting,

1161
01:28:44,018 --> 01:28:46,213
but almost every part
of their lives.

1162
01:28:47,588 --> 01:28:49,351
That's why they were Lunas.

1163
01:28:50,525 --> 01:28:55,258
They would not gather plants or save next
year's seeds until the moon said so.

1164
01:29:00,568 --> 01:29:02,365
I thought of my father too.

1165
01:29:03,071 --> 01:29:04,936
His wild and restless spirit,

1166
01:29:05,006 --> 01:29:07,133
that forever
reached out somewhere.

1167
01:29:08,009 --> 01:29:12,275
I didn't know if his or my mother's
blood would claim me in the end.

1168
01:29:13,948 --> 01:29:17,247
But the bad dreams that had
plagued me, did not come.

1169
01:29:36,471 --> 01:29:39,463
Antonio! A letter
from your mother!

1170
01:29:51,018 --> 01:29:53,145
They'll come for you
in a few days.

1171
01:29:54,155 --> 01:29:55,417
School starts early this year.

1172
01:29:55,490 --> 01:29:57,424
It comes early every year.

1173
01:30:00,695 --> 01:30:03,061
Your mother says
you do well in school.

1174
01:30:03,131 --> 01:30:05,691
You like school?
Yes, I like it.

1175
01:30:06,167 --> 01:30:07,464
Well, that's good.

1176
01:30:07,535 --> 01:30:09,901
A man of learning can go
far in this world, Antonio.

1177
01:30:11,739 --> 01:30:13,468
It makes us all very proud.

1178
01:30:13,808 --> 01:30:16,641
It's been a long time since
there was an educated Luna.

1179
01:30:18,413 --> 01:30:19,437
I'm Marez.

1180
01:30:20,882 --> 01:30:22,577
(CHUCKLING) That's right.

1181
01:30:22,950 --> 01:30:25,077
You're a Marez first,
and then Luna.

1182
01:30:25,686 --> 01:30:27,347
But I just wanted
to say that, ah,

1183
01:30:27,422 --> 01:30:28,942
that we're very pleased
with your work.

1184
01:30:29,424 --> 01:30:31,585
We know that you must choose
what you'll do as a man,

1185
01:30:32,026 --> 01:30:34,051
but if you ever decide
to become a farmer,

1186
01:30:34,128 --> 01:30:35,152
you'll be welcome here.

1187
01:30:35,830 --> 01:30:38,628
This earth that was your
mother's will be yours.

1188
01:30:38,699 --> 01:30:40,792
MAN: Pedro, can I
see you a minute?

1189
01:30:43,671 --> 01:30:46,265
There's trouble in town.

1190
01:30:46,808 --> 01:30:47,968
(INDISTINCT)

1191
01:30:50,211 --> 01:30:51,269
PEDRO: Antonio!

1192
01:30:51,679 --> 01:30:54,978
Something's come up, so we'll drive
you home today after supper!

1193
01:30:55,583 --> 01:30:58,211
There's only a few hours
of work left to do,

1194
01:30:58,286 --> 01:31:01,551
so, go to your grandfather's
house and pack your clothes.

1195
01:31:02,857 --> 01:31:04,791
Hey, if anyone asks
why you're back early,

1196
01:31:04,859 --> 01:31:07,054
tell 'em you got time off for
being such a good worker.

1197
01:31:07,395 --> 01:31:08,555
Okay, tío.

1198
01:31:29,984 --> 01:31:33,010
(CURSING IN SPANISH)

1199
01:31:49,904 --> 01:31:51,132
(GRUNTS)

1200
01:31:57,211 --> 01:32:00,374
I hope you've broken
your neck, you little jerk!

1201
01:32:01,349 --> 01:32:04,648
Eso vieja bruja has killed
another of my daughters!

1202
01:32:04,919 --> 01:32:06,784
I'll avenge her death tonight!

1203
01:32:08,322 --> 01:32:09,448
Do you hear me?

1204
01:32:12,159 --> 01:32:13,990
Don't you crawl about!

1205
01:32:14,762 --> 01:32:18,095
The coyotes will have sport
when they devour you tonight!

1206
01:32:18,366 --> 01:32:20,857
You, hijo de la bruja!

1207
01:32:23,004 --> 01:32:25,871
ADULT ANTONIO: My uncles
had betrayed Ultima before,

1208
01:32:27,074 --> 01:32:29,167
so I ran to save her myself.

1209
01:32:34,515 --> 01:32:36,380
I ran to save the spirit

1210
01:32:36,450 --> 01:32:40,284
that protected us from the evil
that men brought to our hills.

1211
01:32:41,188 --> 01:32:44,419
That had been there when the
heavens looked on in silence.

1212
01:32:45,726 --> 01:32:49,287
I ran from the river
and took to the llano.

1213
01:32:59,307 --> 01:33:00,569
(PANTING)

1214
01:33:15,456 --> 01:33:17,014
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

1215
01:33:50,758 --> 01:33:51,816
PEDRO: Antonio!

1216
01:33:53,561 --> 01:33:55,791
GABRIEL: Pedro? Qué? Qué pasa?
PEDRO: Is Antonio here?

1217
01:33:56,430 --> 01:33:57,419
Qué pasa?

1218
01:33:57,498 --> 01:33:59,796
Aquí! Tenorio's here!

1219
01:34:04,538 --> 01:34:05,527
(GUN CLICKING)

1220
01:34:07,942 --> 01:34:09,000
(OWL SCREECHING)

1221
01:34:12,913 --> 01:34:14,471
Toño!
Antonio!

1222
01:34:17,718 --> 01:34:19,039
MARIA: Antonio!
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1223
01:34:20,721 --> 01:34:22,120
(GUNSHOT)

1224
01:34:29,263 --> 01:34:30,525
(PANTING)

1225
01:34:31,499 --> 01:34:32,796
Oh, my God!

1226
01:34:41,208 --> 01:34:43,642
Ultima?
Where's Ultima?

1227
01:34:45,246 --> 01:34:46,235
Antonio!

1228
01:34:46,414 --> 01:34:47,642
Antonio!

1229
01:34:59,293 --> 01:35:00,885
May God help me.

1230
01:35:21,015 --> 01:35:22,141
The owl!

1231
01:35:22,216 --> 01:35:23,513
It's dead.

1232
01:35:24,251 --> 01:35:25,479
Not dead.

1233
01:35:27,188 --> 01:35:29,748
Winging its way to a new place,

1234
01:35:30,624 --> 01:35:31,989
a new time.

1235
01:35:38,232 --> 01:35:39,995
When I was a child,

1236
01:35:41,235 --> 01:35:43,999
a wise old man gave me the owl

1237
01:35:44,705 --> 01:35:48,903
as a... As a bond
to the time

1238
01:35:50,044 --> 01:35:52,342
and harmony of the universe.

1239
01:35:57,251 --> 01:36:01,051
Evil men create disharmony

1240
01:36:02,389 --> 01:36:06,257
that reaches out
and destroys life.

1241
01:36:11,398 --> 01:36:13,161
But it passes away,

1242
01:36:14,969 --> 01:36:16,527
it passes away.

1243
01:36:22,376 --> 01:36:24,173
Gather my medicines,

1244
01:36:27,648 --> 01:36:31,106
and burn them
somewhere on the river.

1245
01:36:31,819 --> 01:36:33,116
Everything.

1246
01:36:34,655 --> 01:36:37,954
But take the owl now
into the hills,

1247
01:36:39,994 --> 01:36:41,484
and bury it at a...

1248
01:36:43,731 --> 01:36:45,665
At a forked juniper tree.

1249
01:36:47,968 --> 01:36:49,060
Go...

1250
01:36:50,204 --> 01:36:51,535
Go quickly.

1251
01:36:54,275 --> 01:36:55,867
Bless me, Ultima.

1252
01:37:00,581 --> 01:37:02,981
In the name of all that's good

1253
01:37:04,852 --> 01:37:08,413
and strong and beautiful

1254
01:37:13,994 --> 01:37:15,359
I bless you.

1255
01:37:18,899 --> 01:37:19,991
Go.

1256
01:37:21,735 --> 01:37:22,759
Go, quickly.

1257
01:37:55,202 --> 01:37:56,396
Grande...

1258
01:38:04,011 --> 01:38:05,342
(SNIFFLES)

1259
01:38:23,397 --> 01:38:26,662
ADULT ANTONIO: My father
built a fine pine coffin,

1260
01:38:27,268 --> 01:38:30,669
and people came from miles
around to mourn La Grande,

1261
01:38:31,372 --> 01:38:33,738
her cures and her magic.

1262
01:38:35,442 --> 01:38:38,138
But, I knew to look
beyond their sadness.

1263
01:38:39,380 --> 01:38:43,009
Ultima taught us how to make
strength from our experiences.

1264
01:38:43,083 --> 01:38:45,176
To hold wonder in our lives.

1265
01:38:46,387 --> 01:38:50,551
She taught us that the eternal
soul expands by embracing life,

1266
01:38:50,624 --> 01:38:54,116
and all that happens,
both good and evil.

1267
01:38:58,198 --> 01:38:59,859
No, I did not cry.

1268
01:39:01,068 --> 01:39:03,662
Her voice is everywhere.

